                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong>: A creature with blood moves through a patch of lifeleech crystals.</p>\n<p><strong> Effect</strong>:&nbsp; The crystals twist and slash, animating and cutting into the creature as it walks, dealing [[/r 5d8 #slashing]] slashing damage. The creature must attempt a DC 28 Reflex saving throw.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong>: The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong>: The creature takes full damage and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.4D2KBtexWXa6oUMR]{Drained} 1.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong>: The creature takes double damage and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionspf2e.4D2KBtexWXa6oUMR]{Drained} 2.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong>: As failure, plus the creature’s blood causes fresh growth. A new 10-foot-square patch of lifeleech crystals grows in an adjacent space to the current patch of crystals.</p>",
